&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Upward Health is an in-home, multidisciplinary medical group providing 24/7 whole-person care. Our clinical team treats physical, behavioral, and social health needs when and where a patient needs help. Everyone on our team from our doctors, nurses, and Care Specialists to our HR, Technology, and Business Services staff are driven by a desire to improve the lives of our patients. We are able to treat a wide range of needs – everything from addressing poorly controlled blood sugar to combatting anxiety to accessing medically tailored meals – because we know that health requires care for the whole person. It’s no wonder 98% of patients report being fully satisfied with Upward Health!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title &amp;amp; Role Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Care Management Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; responsible for driving the strategy, design, and delivery of technology solutions that support clinical care operations across the Upward Health organization. This role focuses primarily on solutions built in &lt;strong&gt;Salesforce Health Cloud&lt;/strong&gt;, with occasional collaboration on integrations or workflows involving other clinical applications. The Product Manager partners closely with clinical leaders, care teams, and operational stakeholders to deeply understand pain points, translate those into operational needs into well-defined product requirements, and guide solutions from concept through delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This individual works closely with the Product Development team—including Product Analysts and Salesforce Developers—to prioritize work, define acceptance criteria, manage scope, and ensure high-quality releases. The Care Management Product Manager will own the product roadmap for care management system capabilities, balancing new requests against strategic priorities while maintaining visibility into delivery progress and outcomes. The role requires strong stakeholder engagement, comfort navigating ambiguity, and the ability to establish structure and product discipline in a fast-evolving healthcare environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing healthcare or clinical technology products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong familiarity with care management workflows and clinical operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with &lt;strong&gt;Salesforce Health Cloud&lt;/strong&gt; or comparable care management platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate complex operational needs into clear product requirements and user stories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing detailed acceptance criteria and working closely with engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong stakeholder management and cross-functional communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing product roadmaps and prioritization frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to track product performance using metrics and outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing scope, timelines, and delivery expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong presentation and communication skills for executive and stakeholder updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in agile or iterative product development environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously in a dynamic environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Behaviors:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of clinical workflows and care team pain points to inform product strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary product owner for Care Management capabilities, primarily within Salesforce Health Cloud&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with clinical stakeholders to define requirements, document workflows, and develop clear acceptance criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate stake

&lt;p id=&quot;isPasted&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Upward Health is an in-home, multidisciplinary medical group providing 24/7 whole-person care. Our clinical team treats physical, behavioral, and social health needs when and where a patient needs help. Everyone on our team from our doctors, nurses, and Care Specialists to our HR, Technology, and Business Services staff are driven by a desire to improve the lives of our patients. We are able to treat a wide range of needs – everything from addressing poorly controlled blood sugar to combatting anxiety to accessing medically tailored meals – because we know that health requires care for the whole person. It’s no wonder 98% of patients report being fully satisfied with Upward Health!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title &amp;amp; Role Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Care Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a key member of the team responsible for delivering chronic care management to high-complexity patients. The Care Specialist primarily works in patients&#39; homes and communities (90% of the time) and engages in virtual care (10% of the time). This role involves direct outreach to patients, guiding them through the enrollment process, facilitating virtual appointments with providers, and ensuring that patients adhere to care plans. By building relationships, coordinating care, and providing education, the Care Specialist plays a critical role in promoting health, preventing unnecessary hospitalizations, and improving patient outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of relevant work experience (e.g., Community Health Worker, Peer Support Specialist, Medical Assistant, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A valid driver’s license, auto liability insurance, and reliable transportation to travel within the assigned territory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in chronic care management or working with chronically ill/elderly patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technologically proficient with basic computer skills (typing, using EMR systems).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with motivational interviewing, trauma-informed care, and care coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal communication skills with the ability to engage patients and team members effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize tasks, manage schedules, and work independently in an unstructured environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multi-lingual skills are a plus but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior home care experience is beneficial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Behaviors:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adaptability &amp;amp; Resilience:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in unstructured environments and pivot as needed to meet patient needs. Demonstrates perseverance in challenging situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Self-Starter &amp;amp; Motivation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively takes initiative in managing patient care and outreach. Willingness to learn and adapt to new processes and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Empathy &amp;amp; Compassion:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with individuals from diverse backgrounds and understand their complex needs. Skilled in building rapport through motivational interviewing and other patient-centered communication techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accountability &amp;amp; Integrity:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates personal responsibility and takes ownership of tasks, ensuring accuracy and timeliness in all activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
